      "content": "wait what? goblins? i think i misread that. i'm just trying to study for my engineering exam, i'm not really looking for stories about moss or goblins. \n\ncan we just stay on the technical side? you were talking about ductility and how steel prevents that sudden catastrophic failure. how exactly does the bond between the rebar and the concrete work to ensure that the tension is actually transferred to the steel instead of the concrete just cracking around it?",
